 <body>
  <p>Adobe Experience Manager (AEM) content fragments are <a href="../../../assets/using/content-fragments.md">created and managed as page-independent assets</a>.</p> 
  <p>They allow you to create channel-neutral content, together with (possibly channel-specific) variations. You can then use these fragments, and their variations, when authoring your content pages.</p> 
  <note>
   <p>The full functionality of Content Fragment Management is not available in classic UI. See <a href="../../../sites/authoring/using/content-fragments.md">Page Authoring with Content Fragments</a> in the standard authoring documentation.</p> 
   <p>The Content Fragment component can be seen in the classic UI sidekick, but further functions are not available.</p> 
  </note>
